@piiswrong Getting started is a **section**, not a **page**. So these documents are **not** in the same page. They share a **nav** item. Nav items should point to categories, not pages (it should be somewhat balanced tree). Eventually Getting started will also handle the more nuts and bolts type tutorials (what's in basics now) but for now we're just going to have these two pages. 

Yes the images need to be sized properly, we've already discussed this above in the comment thread. 

Regarding the image repo, this seems like a horrible design decision. We shouldn't have dependencies among (as many as 3!) repos to make a single change to the site. It's fine to play by that for now. In the long run I think it's unacceptable.

